<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>Inline Elements</title>
        <style type="text/css">
            * { margin: 0; padding: 0; }
            body { width: 800px; height: 600px; background: #ffffff; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 16px; padding: 10px; }
            p { margin: 10px 0; line-height: 1.8; }
            .bg-yellow { background: #ffff00; padding: 2px 6px; }
            .bg-cyan { background: #00ffff; padding: 4px 8px; border: 1px solid #009999; }
            .bg-pink { background: #ffccee; padding: 2px 4px; border: 2px dashed #cc0066; }
            a { color: #0000cc; background: #eeeeff; padding: 2px 4px; text-decoration: underline; }
            em { color: #006600; background: #eeffee; font-style: italic; }
            strong { color: #cc0000; background: #ffeeee; font-weight: bold; }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Normal text with a <span class="bg-yellow">yellow span</span> and a <span class="bg-cyan">cyan bordered span</span> inline.</p>
        <p>This has <a href="#">a styled link</a> and <em>emphasized green text</em> and <strong>strong red text</strong>.</p>
        <p><span class="bg-pink">Dashed border span</span> next to <span class="bg-yellow">yellow</span> next to <span class="bg-cyan">cyan</span>.</p>
    </body>
</html>
